local ensure_installed = vim.tbl_keys(servers or {})
vim.list_extend(ensure_installed, {
  'stylua',        -- Lua formatter (kickstart's default)
  'tflint',        -- Terraform linter
  -- Optional DevOps extras — uncomment as you need them:
  -- 'hadolint',   -- Dockerfile linter
  -- 'yamlfmt',    -- YAML formatter
  -- 'shfmt',      -- shell script formatter
  -- 'shellcheck', -- shell script linter
})
A few notes so this doesn't surprise you later:
terraform fmt doesn't get added here — it's part of the terraform CLI binary itself, which you already installed via Homebrew/winget. Conform just shells out to whichever terraform is on your PATH. So formatting works as long as terraform --version works in your shell.
terraformls lives in the servers = {} table above this snippet, not here. The pattern is: LSPs (things that speak Language Server Protocol) → servers. Linters/formatters (things that just produce output) → this list_extend. Mason installs both, but kickstart wires them up through different mechanisms (nvim-lspconfig for the first, conform/nvim-lint for the second).
After you save and restart, run :Mason to see the install status — green checkmarks mean Mason fetched them successfully. If tflint shows red, run :MasonInstall tflint manually once and check :checkhealth mason for hints (usually it's a missing dependency like Go or curl).
